body.name: Cooler Master HAF 500 High Airflow ATX Mid-Tower, Mesh Front Panel, Dual 200mm Customizable ARG Lighting Fans, Rotatable GPU Fan, USB 3.2 Gen 2 Type C and Tempered Glass (H500-KGNN-S00)
features: Mesh Front Panel: Large filtered intakes promotes high airflow, keeping internal components running at optimal temperature.
Dual 200mm ARGB Fans: The HAF series iconic 200mm ARGB fans move high volumes of air quietly and effectively due to their large size.
Rotatable GPU Fan: A 120mm rotatable fan positioned on top of the HDD cage, provides dedicated GPU cooling to ensure maximum performance.
USB 3.2 Gen 2 Type C Support: USB 3.2 Gen 2 Type C ports built into the I/O panel allows multi-purpose, streamlined data transmission.
Screwless & Tool-Free TG Side Panel Design: The tempered glass side panel is secured with pins for easy removal without the use of tools.
body.description: Cooler Master’s classic HAF series is making a return with HAF 500. Built for high airflow and peak performance, the HAF 500 boasts iconic 200mm large intake ARGB fans, ensuring unparalleled intake and cooling efficiency. The chassis features a dedicated GPU fan, adjustable to various GPU lengths. Ample clearance for dual 360mm radiators on the top and front panel accommodates the most advanced water cooling setups. Tool-less side panels and a removable top panel facilitates simplified, hassle-free component installation without the need to struggle with small spaces.

The joy of making and creating something uniquely yours in form and function and, of course, the thrill of bringing your creation to life without melting your components. HAF 500 Homecoming Classic Cooler Master’s classic HAF series is making a return with HAF 500. Built for high airflow and peak performance, the HAF 500 boasts iconic 200mm large intake ARGB fans, ensuring unparalleled intake and cooling efficiency. The chassis features a dedicated GPU fan, adjustable to various GPU lengths. Dual 200mm ARGB Fans Mesh Front Panel Rotatable GPU Fan ARGB/PWM Hub Removable Top Panel Screwless & Tool-Free TG Side Panel Design USB 3.2 Gen 2 Type C Support Versatile Cooling Options

Mesh Front Panel The presence of large filtered intakes ensures a high airflow environment, effectively maintaining optimal temperatures for internal components. Versatile Cooling Enjoy high compatibility for liquid-cooled systems with support for up to seven 120/140mm fans and the ability to accommodate dual 360mm radiators. Components Clearance This case supports CPU coolers with a maximum of 167mm (H), GPU up to 410mm (L), and PSU with a maximum of 180mm (L). Dual 200mm ARGB Fans The revised curve blade design is specifically tailored to maximize performance, ensuring low temperatures and minimal noise levels, even during extreme overclocking scenarios.

Addressable RGB Our intuitive LED detection automatically provides default Addressable RGB spectrum lighting or full ARGB customization via a 3-pin header connection. Rotatable GPU Fan Maximize GPU performance with a dedicated 120mm rotatable fan positioned on top of the HDD cage. It efficiently directs airflow towards the GPU, maintaining optimal temperatures. Removable Top Panel For enhanced access during the assembly of cooling solutions, the top panel can be easily and completely removed, allowing for convenient handling of components. ARGB/PWM Hub Simplify cable management with the included HUB, 5 ARGB and 4 PWM ports. This convenient allows you to control fans with a single connector for power and PWM.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Quality construction and attractive design in a mid size case.
reviews.reviewText: I built a computer for my daughter using this case and it turned out extremely well. I used an ATX motherboard, 850 watt PSU, large air cooler for CPU, and a full size RTX 3080 GPU. The case is solidly constructed, made with quality materials, and easily accommodates standard size components. Being a mid size case, I'd recommend it for an average or common component set. If you're going for super compact and light, you don't need a case of this size or weight. If you're building a mega computer with huge liquid coolers and such, probably you should look for something specifically designed for that. But for the majority of self built computers, this is an awesome case that will give you zero problems with your build.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 16, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Really well constructed case, excellent airflow with plenty of vents. Front fans provide plenty of internal air to allow cooling out the back and top exhaust areas. Space behind motherboard has room to hide cables with a lot of options for internal routing where needed.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 15, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Overall a solid product. I previously owned the HAF 932 and upgraded to this after more than a decade. Solid modern case with lots of space inside. Front fans are pretty big, but the stock fans are not that quiet. They're ok, but at this price point that's to be expected. Magnetic filter on top is nice for keeping dust out. Plenty of space inside for larger components and keeping wiring out of sight.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 7, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Facil para armar y precioso
reviews.reviewText: Super facil para armar con bastante espacio dentro del case y detrás también para hacer un buen acomodo de cables,en mi opinión muy bonito,lo único que encontré no muy bueno es la cablería delantera,se nota mucho y no hicieron nada para taparla lo más posible,aún así no me molesta y pienso vale muchísimo la pena tener uno de estos,lo recomiendo...

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars As cool as it looks
reviews.reviewText: It's exactly as advertised. My son was in awe, and so was I when I completed his build.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 19, 2023
Reviewed in the United States on January 24, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Front Fans require padding for silence.
reviews.reviewText: Front fans require some padding to stay quiet. I used pads left over Evo 212. Noctua rubber screws won't work for 200mm fans. Interestingly they are MF200R RGB, but they don't come with rubber pads, despite stand-alone product have them. Could be older generation. This case can be a good buy under heavy discount. Hub is PWM but front fans are not.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 8, 2022

reviews.reviewText: This haf 500 case has good and bad features. The dual 200mm front fans are "haf" blocked by the 120/140mm chassis fan mounts. Airflow will be affected even at full 800rpm. No front intake filter means more dust will enter the case. The perforated mesh is not fine enough to be used as a dust filter. The picture in the ad says it supports 140mm exhaust fan but only 120mm can fit. The gpu swivel fan on top of the hard drive bay seems nice but has no argb. It would have been nice if the hard drive bay had a cover. The removable plastic psu shroud is nice for those who want to show their high end psu or have air intake from the inside of the case to help with airflow. The 200mm fans has a slight wobble at any speed. It's a nice big case but the small fan mounts on the front ruined the potential high airflow. This is basically an old case back from 2010 that has rgb lighting and a glass side panel to make it look modern.
